# Armada App

## Required workflow

1. **Read** `../armada-crowdfund/ARMADA_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` before writing or editing UI.
2. **Follow `accessibility-a11y.mdc`** — strictly apply [A11Y.md](https://github.com/fecarrico/A11Y.md/blob/main/docs/en/A11Y.md) for all frontend work.
3. **Never hardcode** hex colors, raw `px` spacing/sizing, or font sizes — use CSS custom properties from `src/styles/tokens.css`.
4. **Verify token names** in `src/styles/tokens.css` before using any `var(--…)`.
5. **Run `npm run build`** before marking any task complete.

## Tokens

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/tokens/armada-tokens.json` | Token Studio source (synced from armada-crowdfund) |
| `src/constants/depositChains.ts` | `DepositChainId` type + network icons (app-owned) |
| `src/styles/tokens.css` | Primitives + semantic colors (synced from armada-crowdfund) |
| `src/styles/typography.css` | Composite typography classes (synced from armada-poc `@armada/ui`) |

After token changes in sibling repos, run `npm run tokens:sync` (also runs automatically before `npm run build`).

## Styling

- CSS Modules per component (`Component.module.css`).
- Prefer semantic tokens (`--semantic-*`); use primitives when no semantic alias exists.
- Border radius and font-size primitives are unitless — wrap with `calc(var(--token) * 1px)`.

## Dev

- `npm run dev` → http://localhost:5177/
- `npm run build` → `npm run tokens:sync && tsc && vite build`
